  "text": "All results for 125 I-lipoprotein catabolism were normalized to cellular protein [CITATION_1] , which averaged 65 g per well for both wild-type CHO-K1 cells and transfected CHO lines. LpL-dependent catabolism was calculated by subtracting the values obtained in the absence of LpL (LpL-independent catabolism) from those obtained in the presence of LpL (total catabolism). We obtained essentially identical results when LpL-independent values were determined by assessing catabolism in the presence of a low concentration of heparin (66 g/ml) that is known to displace LpL from cell-surface HSPGs [CITATION_2] .",
